===============================================================
Tag name: ctsm5.3.034
Originator(s): rgknox (Ryan Knox)
Date: Thu Mar 27 16:03:56 MDT 2025
One-line Summary: Fixes to enable passing FATES two-stream ERS and ERI restart tests.

Purpose and description of changes
----------------------------------

This set of changes refactors the calculation of zenith angles by putting them
into a separate call, and enables FATES to make updates to its albedo solve
on all timesteps regardless of the doalb flag. The FATES side of the code
will not perform calculations unless the zenith angle is positive anyway.
These refactors were necessary to have restart tests passing for FATES
when two-stream radiation is enabled. Further, the zenith angle boundary
condition is now passed to fates at the column level, which is more
scale consistent.

Significant changes to scientifically-supported configurations
--------------------------------------------------------------

This set of changes to ctsm code does not make any significant changes that affect model results.
This set of changes does update the pointer to the FATES tag, which since the previous
ctsm api change with fates, has improved code stability for photosynthesis. Those
changes result in non-trivial but non-significant deviations in answers in FATES
configurations.

There are no changes to non-FATES answers.


Bugs fixed
----------

List of CTSM issues fixed:
 Fixes 2903: FATES doesn't work in branch runs
 Fixes 2325: ERS FatesColdTwoStreamNoCompFixedBioGeo Restart Test Fails

Notes of particular relevance for users
---------------------------------------

This set of changes is a necessary milestone towards FATES using
two-stream radiation as its default configuration.

Notes of particular relevance for developers:
---------------------------------------------
Changes to tests or testing:
 Added ERS_D_Ld20_f45_f45_mg37_I2000Clm50FatesRs_FatesColdTwoStreamNoCompFixedBioGeo to aux_clm

Testing summary:
----------------

  regular tests (aux_clm: https://github.com/ESCOMP/CTSM/wiki/System-Testing-Guide#pre-merge-system-testing):

    derecho ----- OK (new passes)
    izumi ------- OK

Answer changes
--------------

As mentioned above, answers only changed for FATES.
Answers changed trivially due to zenith angle coupling changes and updates to the FATES tag.


Other details
-------------

The FATES git-fleximod pointer was updated to sci.1.82.3_api.39.0.0

Pull Requests that document the changes (include PR ids):
2949: https://github.com/ESCOMP/CTSM/pull/2949

===============================================================
===============================================================
Tag name: ctsm5.3.033
Originator(s): wwieder, slevis (Will Wieder, Sam Levis, UCAR/TSS)
Date: Wed 19 Mar 2025 02:43:55 PM MDT
One-line Summary: Add new mimics_fi param = frac of litter inputs bypassing litter pools

Purpose and description of changes
----------------------------------

 Summary from the PR: removes NPP control on turnover
                      fixes density dependent control on turnover
                      adds litterfall fluxes that bypass litter pools, directly contributing to SOM

 This PR also addresses the issue of varying microbial turnover with depth.

Significant changes to scientifically-supported configurations
--------------------------------------------------------------

Does this tag change answers significantly for any of the following physics configurations?
(Details of any changes will be given in the "Answer changes" section below.)

    [Put an [X] in the box for any configuration with significant answer changes.]

[ ] clm6_0

[ ] clm5_0

[ ] ctsm5_0-nwp

[ ] clm4_5


